A1  - Yan, Juan-juan
Y1  - 2011//
N2  - OBJECTIVE: To analyze clinical epidemiology characteristics of HFMD in children from April 2010 to October in Hangzhou., METHODS: 1848 HFMD hospital patients are admitted to clinical epidemiological analysis., RESULTS: Onset ages of HFMD primarily under 3 years, boys more than girls, social above diasporas, rural above town. The highest peak in 5-7 months. Mostly clinical symptoms are mild, the prognosis is good., CONCLUSION: HFMD has obvious susceptible population and susceptibility season. Increase health interventions to susceptible regions and the crowd in popular season, early detection, active therapy, most prognosis is good.
